567
00:27:31,910 --> 00:27:34,220
再說了  就我們倆  空口無憑
Besides, ‭it's your word against mine.

568
00:27:45,870 --> 00:27:48,460
好了  阿利先生
All right, uh, Mr. Alley, uh,

569
00:27:48,460 --> 00:27:51,380
我們得為下一位證人安排一下
we need to make accommodations for your next witness.

570
00:27:51,390 --> 00:27:52,100
對嗎
Is that correct?

571
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:54,000
-是  主席先生  -行
- Yes, Mr. Chairman. - All right.

572
00:27:54,180 --> 00:27:57,460
告訴大家  我們得準備一下房間
For those who don't know, we need to prepare the room.

573
00:27:57,460 --> 00:28:00,640
員工會收好你們的手機
Uh, the clerk is going to collect your, uh, cellphones,

574
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:03,060
手表  密鑰卡  一切電子設備
watches, key fobs -- anything electrical.

575
00:28:03,060 --> 00:28:04,930
如果你們不想這么做
If you prefer not to,

576
00:28:04,930 --> 00:28:07,890
請把東西放到房間之外保管好  謝謝
please secure your items outside this room. Thank you.

577
00:28:07,890 --> 00:28:09,240
謝謝你們的理解
Thank you for understanding.

578
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:11,100
你的手機  先生
Your phone, sir?

579
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:12,460
我留在車里了
I left it in the car.

580
00:29:02,010 --> 00:29:03,680
-不好意思  -抱歉
- Oh. Excuse me. - Sorry.

581
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,230
-那是你的  -謝謝
- That's yours. - Thanks.

582
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,620
請舉起你的右手
Please raise your right hand.

583
00:29:20,650 --> 00:29:23,600
你發誓或確認道出事實  沒有隱瞞
Do you swear or affirm to tell the truth, the whole truth,

584
00:29:23,610 --> 00:29:25,020
只說事實嗎
and nothing but the truth?

585
00:29:25,170 --> 00:29:26,040
是的
I do.

586
00:29:31,250 --> 00:29:32,470
你能說出你的姓名嗎
Could you state your name?

587
00:29:32,650 --> 00:29:34,280
查爾斯·L·麥吉爾
Charles L. McGill.

588
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:38,490
我是哈姆林麥吉爾聯合律所的高級合伙人
I'm a senior partner at the law firm of Hamlin, Hamlin, McGill.

589
00:29:39,210 --> 00:29:40,570
法院書記官能聽得見嗎
Can the court reporter hear me?

590
00:29:40,650 --> 00:29:42,480
聽得見  先生  我能聽清楚
Yes, sir. I can hear you fine.

591
00:29:42,610 --> 00:29:44,500
麥吉爾先生  我盡量簡短一點
Mr. McGill, I'll try to be brief.

592
00:29:44,700 --> 00:29:46,280
我們不必詳述入室行竊
We don't need to dwell on the burglary

593
00:29:46,290 --> 00:29:48,040
或是你遭受侵襲的過程
or the assault that you suffered.

594
00:29:48,050 --> 00:29:49,520
謝謝  我很感激
Thank you. I appreciate that.

595
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:51,740
我想知道關于這盤磁帶的事
What I would like to hear about is this tape.

596
00:29:52,020 --> 00:29:53,430
什么迫使你錄下了這盤磁帶
What compelled you to make it?

597
00:29:53,780 --> 00:29:56,770
我懷疑我弟弟篡改了我當時經手的
I had a suspicion my brother had tampered with documents

598
00:29:56,770 --> 00:29:58,250
一個案子的文件
in a case I was working on.

599
00:29:58,260 --> 00:29:59,660
他為什么要這么做
And why would he do that?

600
00:29:59,790 --> 00:30:01,780
聽起來不怎么像兄弟所為
Doesn't sound particularly brotherly.

601
00:30:01,780 --> 00:30:04,400
我認為他希望篡改的文件
I believe it was his hope that the tainted documents

602
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:08,670
會讓客戶打消讓我為其辯護的念頭
would cause the client to become disillusioned with my representation

603
00:30:08,740 --> 00:30:11,750
而聘用他們之前的律師  韋克斯勒小姐
and return to their previous attorney, Ms. Wexler. ‭

604
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:15,420
這里我要說明一下  他們如愿以償了
Which, I should note, is precisely what happened.

605
00:30:15,420 --> 00:30:16,500
反對
Objection.

606
00:30:16,500 --> 00:30:19,000
我不是說韋克斯勒小姐對吉米的行為知情
I'm not saying Ms. Wexler knew what Jimmy was doing

607
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,540
或是參與其中
or had any involvement.

608
00:30:20,660 --> 00:30:22,690
我只是指出結果的確如此
I'm only stating that it happened.

609
00:30:23,220 --> 00:30:24,170
關于你對詹姆斯的懷疑
Did you have any evidence

610
00:30:24,170 --> 00:30:26,170
你有證據證明嗎
to support your suspicions about James?

611
00:30:26,170 --> 00:30:28,300
沒有  我的弟弟
No. My brother,

612
00:30:28,300 --> 00:30:31,040
拋開別的不講  聰明過人
whatever else can be said of him, can be quite clever.

613
00:30:31,250 --> 00:30:33,490
將自己的行徑掩蓋得非常好
Did an excellent job of covering his tracks.

614
00:30:33,500 --> 00:30:34,530
反對
Objection.

615
00:30:34,530 --> 00:30:36,880
證人剛承認了沒有相關證據
The witness has admitted there's no corroborating evidence

616
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:39,030
證明當事人犯下如上罪行
this supposed crime even occurred.

617
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:40,870
我想聽聽他要說什么
I'd like to hear what he has to say.

618
00:30:42,570 --> 00:30:43,940
請繼續
We're going to continue.

619
00:30:43,990 --> 00:30:47,410
你也可以進行盤問  韋克斯勒女士
Uh, we'll extend you the same latitude on cross, Ms. Wexler.

620
00:30:48,820 --> 00:30:50,160
繼續  麥吉爾先生
Go on, Mr. McGill.

621
00:30:50,670 --> 00:30:51,810
由于沒有確鑿證據
Without physical evidence,

622
00:30:51,810 --> 00:30:53,730
我覺得能錄下他承認罪行
I felt that ‭a recorded confession --

623
00:30:53,730 --> 00:30:56,090
如果我能錄到的話  是最好的機會
if I could get one -- was my best bet.

624
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:58,800
就本身而言  我知道這盤磁帶會沒有那么周密
On its own, I knew the tape would be somewhat flimsy,

625
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:00,130
但是個開始
but it was a start.

626
00:31:00,180 --> 00:31:02,990
為更為縝密的立案打下基礎
A foundation for a more ironclad case.

627
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,760
我猜吉米肯定覺得
I suppose that Jimmy must have felt

628
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:08,060
那盤磁帶本身是一個有力的證據
the tape was decisive evidence on its own.

629
00:31:08,060 --> 00:31:09,980
不然的話  他也不會闖進我家將它毀壞
Otherwise, he wouldn't have broken in to destroy it.

630
00:31:09,980 --> 00:31:11,920
反對  還是任意猜測
Objection. More speculation.

631
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:13,710
他怎么能知道吉米腦中的想法
How can he know what was going on in Jimmy's head?

632
00:31:13,710 --> 00:31:15,860
反對有效  我們只需要了解事情經過
Sustained. We just need to hear what happened,

633
00:31:15,860 --> 00:31:16,490
麥吉爾先生
Mr. McGill.

634
00:31:17,020 --> 00:31:18,550
很抱歉
I-I apologize.

635
00:31:19,180 --> 00:31:21,720
我給我弟弟錄了音  對他進行立案
I recorded my brother to build a case against him.

636
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:23,170
在那時
And at the time,

637
00:31:23,180 --> 00:31:25,540
可以說你的神志是完全清醒的嗎
would you say that you were in possession of your faculties?

638
00:31:25,540 --> 00:31:26,900
恕我冒昧
All due respect, but --

639
00:31:26,900 --> 00:31:29,720
但你在錄音中聽起來有一點神經錯亂
but you do sound somewhat unhinged on the recording.

640
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:31,100
是的  我能理解
Yes, I understand that.

641
00:31:31,110 --> 00:31:33,560
但你所聽到的是戲劇
But what you heard was theater.

642
00:31:33,580 --> 00:31:35,420
一場表演  是我假扮的
A performance, play-acting.

643
00:31:35,750 --> 00:31:39,180
我夸張了我所患疾病的病征
I exaggerated the symptoms of my disease

644
00:31:39,180 --> 00:31:40,540
以獲取事實真相
to extract the truth.

645
00:31:40,540 --> 00:31:42,800
我們能談論一下你的疾病嗎
Can we talk about your disease for a moment?

646
00:31:42,800 --> 00:31:45,300
我希望在場各位都能對其達成共識
I'd like everybody here to be on the same page about it.

647
00:31:45,300 --> 00:31:46,200
當然可以
Of course.

648
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:48,670
有人稱之為EHS
It is sometimes referred to as EHS,

649
00:31:48,670 --> 00:31:50,970
電磁過敏癥
electromagnetic hypersensitivity.

650
00:31:51,270 --> 00:31:54,660
我稱之為對電磁的急性過敏
I describe it as an acute allergy to electromagnetism.

651
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:57,100
這并不是一個常見的病癥  對嗎
It's not a common condition, is it?

652
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,610
我知道這聽起來很奇怪  確實如此
I know it sounds strange. I do.

653
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:02,880
但三十年前  沒有人聽說過花生過敏
But 30 years ago, no one had heard of peanut allergies.

654
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:04,490
但你承認沒有人
But you admit that no one --

655
00:32:04,940 --> 00:32:07,210
沒有醫生對你做出過診斷
no doctor -- has ever diagnosed you.

656
00:32:07,550 --> 00:32:11,220
艾滋病直到1981年才被確診
AIDS was not identified properly until 1981.

657
00:32:11,500 --> 00:32:14,550
直到83年才知道艾滋病是由艾滋病病毒引起
HIV wasn't known as the cause until '83.

658
00:32:14,550 --> 00:32:18,000
這些事情需要時間來解釋  對醫生也是如此
These things take time to unravel, even for doctors.

659
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:19,230
你覺得你的病情
Would you say that your illness

660
00:32:19,230 --> 00:32:21,220
會影響你清晰地思考嗎
affects your ability to think clearly?

661
00:32:21,220 --> 00:32:23,360
不會  只會對我的生理造成影響
No. ‭It affects me physically.

662
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:24,840
會導致我產生劇烈的疼痛
It causes me great pain.

663
00:32:24,850 --> 00:32:26,760
但我還是完全清醒的
However, I'm perfectly lucid.

664
00:32:26,990 --> 00:32:27,950
謝謝
Thank you.

665
00:32:28,490 --> 00:32:31,400
麥吉爾先生  我還有最后一個問題要問你
Mr. McGill, I have ‭only one more question for you.

666
00:32:33,130 --> 00:32:34,560
你恨你的弟弟嗎
Do you hate your brother?

667
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:38,140
一點兒也不恨
Absolutely not.

668
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:40,550
我愛我的弟弟
I love my brother.

669
00:32:41,450 --> 00:32:43,670
吉米本性并不壞
There's nothing malicious in Jimmy.

670
00:32:45,220 --> 00:32:47,410
他總喜歡出于所謂高尚的理由
He has a way of doing the worst things

671
00:32:47,410 --> 00:32:50,170
去做那些惡劣的事情
for reasons ‭that sound almost noble.

672
00:32:51,820 --> 00:32:53,720
但我心中深知
But what I know for sure is that the law

673
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:56,130
法律神圣不可褻瀆
is too important to be toyed with.

674
00:32:56,540 --> 00:32:58,290
這是人類最偉大的成就
It's mankind's greatest achievement

675
00:32:58,290 --> 00:32:59,090
法治
the Rule of Law,

676
00:32:59,090 --> 00:33:00,760
法治的意義就在于  不管你是誰
the idea that, no matter who you are,

677
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:03,390
你的行為都會產生后果
your actions have consequences.

678
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:06,730
而我弟弟對待法律的方式
And the way my brother treats the law --

679
00:33:08,010 --> 00:33:09,340
讓我心碎不已
it breaks my heart.

680
00:33:10,130 --> 00:33:11,300
所以我要這么做
That's why I did what I did.

681
00:33:11,300 --> 00:33:15,620
不是為了傷害他  而是保護我所尊重的東西
Not to hurt him, but to protect something that I hold sacred.

682
00:33:15,620 --> 00:33:17,020
謝謝  麥吉爾先生
Thank you, Mr. McGill.

683
00:33:17,610 --> 00:33:19,380
州律師協會盤問完畢
The State Bar rests.

684
00:33:23,570 --> 00:33:25,630
我覺得我們需要暫停一下
I think we need to put on the brakes.

685
00:33:28,810 --> 00:33:31,810
抱歉  我和我的合伙律師需要時間商討
I'm sorry. My co-counsel and I need a moment to confer.

686
00:33:32,890 --> 00:33:34,630
